00:26:54,705 --> 00:26:57,665
The reason you blow up at your mom…

278
00:27:00,585 --> 00:27:03,264
is to resist the feeling of love.

279
00:27:13,345 --> 00:27:15,665
You're afraid that if you love someone,

280
00:27:18,225 --> 00:27:20,385
you'll lose them.

281
00:27:28,784 --> 00:27:30,425
What happened at the mall…

282
00:27:32,345 --> 00:27:34,225
You were hesitant to enter

283
00:27:36,945 --> 00:27:39,225
not because of bad memories,

284
00:27:45,024 --> 00:27:47,425
but because it's where you lost
your loved one.

285
00:27:49,225 --> 00:27:51,304
You lost him for good.

286
00:28:11,625 --> 00:28:13,665
I never realized that my backstory

287
00:28:14,784 --> 00:28:17,304
had everyone upset.

288
00:28:21,625 --> 00:28:24,984
This must be why he loved to hug me

289
00:28:26,585 --> 00:28:28,185
when he was sad.

290
00:28:30,345 --> 00:28:32,905
It wasn't because he loved the teddy bear,

291
00:28:34,665 --> 00:28:35,825
but because

292
00:28:36,744 --> 00:28:39,585
I represented someone he loved dearly.

293
00:28:43,945 --> 00:28:45,665
I apologize for my lies.

294
00:28:48,264 --> 00:28:49,625
I am actually hurt

295
00:28:50,665 --> 00:28:52,504
and jealous of Tatarn.

296
00:28:54,544 --> 00:28:56,465
Am I a liar now?

297
00:29:02,825 --> 00:29:04,784
But no matter how jealous I am,

298
00:29:05,945 --> 00:29:07,585
I'll always be here.

299
00:29:08,984 --> 00:29:11,105
Whatever reason he had for hugging me,

300
00:29:12,385 --> 00:29:13,825
his hugs

301
00:29:14,504 --> 00:29:16,105
have always been my safe harbor.

302
00:29:25,905 --> 00:29:28,744
Right now, he's in need
of a safe harbor too,

303
00:29:31,425 --> 00:29:32,585
isn't he?

304
00:30:00,425 --> 00:30:03,784
What can I do to help
Nut and his mom reconcile?

305
00:30:04,425 --> 00:30:08,264
At first, you two fought.
Now, Nut and his mom also have issues.

306
00:30:08,345 --> 00:30:10,264
If you won't help, be quiet.

307
00:30:11,064 --> 00:30:13,425
Nut and his mom
have always been like this.

308
00:30:13,504 --> 00:30:14,905
We've spoken about it.

309
00:30:17,185 --> 00:30:18,544
But…

310
00:30:19,585 --> 00:30:20,784
as you know,

311
00:30:21,544 --> 00:30:23,345
he's a complex character.

312
00:30:23,425 --> 00:30:25,625
He has been through a lot.

313
00:30:26,945 --> 00:30:28,225
Right now,

314
00:30:28,744 --> 00:30:30,825
he has a good person supporting him.

315
00:30:31,544 --> 00:30:34,064
I think things are looking better.

316
00:30:35,064 --> 00:30:38,145
They are a family. They'll talk it out.

317
00:30:38,225 --> 00:30:40,145
Someone once told me,

318
00:30:41,544 --> 00:30:43,145
to help another person understand,

319
00:30:43,825 --> 00:30:45,145
you should be honest.

320
00:30:46,185 --> 00:30:48,185
Talking is not that hard.

321
00:30:48,905 --> 00:30:50,145
I'll give it a try.

322
00:30:51,185 --> 00:30:53,225
That lot is now working things out.

323
00:30:53,784 --> 00:30:55,225
This lot needs to do the same.

324
00:30:55,304 --> 00:30:56,865
What's with that lot and this lot?

325
00:30:56,945 --> 00:30:59,225
I'm not talking to you.

326
00:30:59,784 --> 00:31:01,705
I have something important to discuss.

327
00:31:03,625 --> 00:31:04,825
Tomorrow,

328
00:31:05,504 --> 00:31:07,024
will you meet me?

329
00:31:21,585 --> 00:31:23,385
I have something important to discuss.

330
00:31:23,865 --> 00:31:25,024
Tomorrow,

331
00:31:25,784 --> 00:31:27,264
will you meet me?

332
00:31:47,145 --> 00:31:48,064
Hey.

333
00:33:21,865 --> 00:33:22,984
What are you thinking?

334
00:33:24,425 --> 00:33:25,504
Nothing.

335
00:33:33,304 --> 00:33:34,784
If you want me to do that,

336
00:33:35,504 --> 00:33:37,425
let me in first.

337
00:33:40,465 --> 00:33:41,945
Just say what you have to say,

338
00:33:42,425 --> 00:33:43,984
so I can go back to bed.

339
00:33:44,705 --> 00:33:46,385
Why did you want to see me so early?

340
00:33:48,465 --> 00:33:49,665
Let me ask you this.

341
00:33:50,585 --> 00:33:53,465
Do you not like younger guys,
or do you just not like me?

342
00:33:57,865 --> 00:33:59,784
You seem to like me, though.

343
00:34:00,824 --> 00:34:03,185
Why do you pretend
that you have no feelings?

344
00:34:03,945 --> 00:34:05,024
What's wrong?

345
00:34:08,625 --> 00:34:11,744
I want to know what I have to do
for you to give me a chance.

346
00:34:12,384 --> 00:34:13,344
Could it be

347
00:34:13,824 --> 00:34:14,944
that whatever I do,

348
00:34:15,025 --> 00:34:16,344
you're never going to like me

349
00:34:16,944 --> 00:34:18,705
because you can't forget your damn ex?

350
00:34:21,065 --> 00:34:22,384
Come on.

351
00:34:23,025 --> 00:34:24,225
I'm being serious.

352
00:34:27,864 --> 00:34:30,665
Not every kid is like that.

353
00:34:31,145 --> 00:34:33,784
There are many good kids out there.

354
00:34:34,384 --> 00:34:35,784
You don't have to come.

355
00:34:36,465 --> 00:34:39,264
It's just a scratch. It's not deadly.

356
00:34:42,065 --> 00:34:43,744
Once I get my salary,

357
00:34:44,225 --> 00:34:45,744
I'll treat you to a meal.

358
00:34:45,824 --> 00:34:47,545
It's just tiring

359
00:34:48,424 --> 00:34:50,824
when you try your best to please someone,

360
00:34:51,344 --> 00:34:52,585
but they don't even notice.

361
00:34:58,665 --> 00:35:00,384
Why aren't you saying anything?

362
00:35:01,424 --> 00:35:02,864
You're making me nervous.

363
00:35:07,305 --> 00:35:08,465
Gen?

364
00:35:10,665 --> 00:35:11,944
Is it you, Gen?

365
00:35:14,825 --> 00:35:16,305
Win.

366
00:35:25,944 --> 00:35:28,105
When did you get back from Australia?

367
00:35:28,185 --> 00:35:29,825
A month ago.

368
00:35:33,944 --> 00:35:34,785
May I ask

369
00:35:35,585 --> 00:35:37,705
who you prepared this surprise for?

370
00:35:39,105 --> 00:35:39,985
Your boyfriend?

371
00:35:40,864 --> 00:35:43,545
Yes. We met when we were there.

372
00:35:44,025 --> 00:35:45,185
We came back together.

373
00:35:46,145 --> 00:35:48,265
I wanted to make it official.

374
00:35:51,625 --> 00:35:53,625
You and I haven't spoken for three years.

375
00:35:54,545 --> 00:35:55,785
I'm glad

376
00:35:56,265 --> 00:35:57,785
that we can still talk.

377
00:36:00,305 --> 00:36:01,465
Well,

378
00:36:02,185 --> 00:36:03,384
we parted on good terms.

379
00:36:04,345 --> 00:36:05,785
Even though I was upset,

380
00:36:06,465 --> 00:36:07,745
I understood

381
00:36:09,225 --> 00:36:10,944
that you had to plan for your future.

382
00:36:12,384 --> 00:36:14,785
Back then, I didn't treat you well,

383
00:36:15,864 --> 00:36:18,105
but you always treated me like a king.

384
00:36:22,145 --> 00:36:23,145
Actually,

385
00:36:23,625 --> 00:36:25,065
I did many things for you

386
00:36:25,745 --> 00:36:27,305
without you having to ask.

387
00:36:27,864 --> 00:36:29,025
You were head over heels.

388
00:36:32,265 --> 00:36:33,424
Seriously though,

389
00:36:34,065 --> 00:36:35,705
if I could turn back time,

390
00:36:35,785 --> 00:36:37,625
I would still break up with you.

391
00:36:38,665 --> 00:36:39,985
Good relationships

392
00:36:40,825 --> 00:36:42,505
come at the right time.

393
00:36:47,305 --> 00:36:48,625
-Song…
-By the way.

394
00:36:49,384 --> 00:36:50,305
What is it?

395
00:36:50,384 --> 00:36:51,505
I'm all grown up now.

396
00:36:52,464 --> 00:36:53,505
I eat my vegetables,

397
00:36:55,305 --> 00:36:56,864
but I no longer like cabbage.

398
00:36:57,944 --> 00:36:59,464
Do you still grow it?

399
00:36:59,545 --> 00:37:01,864
No, I don't grow it anymore.

400
00:37:01,944 --> 00:37:04,904
I grow ivy gourd now, got it?

401
00:37:24,985 --> 00:37:26,384
I thought you had left.

402
00:37:30,464 --> 00:37:31,384
I can wait.

403
00:37:31,864 --> 00:37:33,384
I just don't want to watch.

404
00:37:34,705 --> 00:37:37,424
You're too sensitive.
It's because you're the youngest son.

405
00:37:40,105 --> 00:37:41,505
What did cabbage boy want?

406
00:37:43,265 --> 00:37:44,665
His name is Marvin.

407
00:37:44,745 --> 00:37:46,105
I don't care what his name is.

408
00:37:46,625 --> 00:37:49,944
Tell me what you were talking about.
Are you getting back together?

409
00:37:50,025 --> 00:37:52,625
Song, are you blind?

410
00:37:52,705 --> 00:37:54,225
This is for his boyfriend.

411
00:37:54,305 --> 00:37:56,345
Where would I fit in?

412
00:38:02,785 --> 00:38:04,904
You didn't answer my question.

413
00:38:09,625 --> 00:38:11,985
Did you have to drag me here
to tell me your answer?

414
00:38:14,585 --> 00:38:16,265
I want to talk this through.

415
00:38:16,345 --> 00:38:17,825
Here.

416
00:38:18,464 --> 00:38:20,944
Drink this to cool yourself down
and listen to me.

417
00:38:21,785 --> 00:38:22,625
Okay?

418
00:38:23,864 --> 00:38:24,745
Okay.

419
00:38:26,225 --> 00:38:29,185
You've talked with your ex.
Now, you have to talk to the new guy.

420
00:38:34,265 --> 00:38:35,785
Why do you keep resisting me?

421
00:38:36,985 --> 00:38:39,825
Why? Did cabbage boy hurt you that badly?

422
00:38:41,545 --> 00:38:43,545
We were in a relationship three years ago.

423
00:38:44,225 --> 00:38:45,705
He was 18 at the time.

424
00:38:46,265 --> 00:38:47,305
I was 24.

425
00:38:49,185 --> 00:38:50,345
Did he ask you out?

426
00:38:51,265 --> 00:38:53,065
No, I approached him.

427
00:38:54,065 --> 00:38:55,424
He was so cute.

428
00:38:59,265 --> 00:39:01,145
I was generous with my money.

429
00:39:01,944 --> 00:39:04,904
He liked eating cabbage, so I grew some.

430
00:39:05,545 --> 00:39:06,985
I even cooked it for him.

431
00:39:14,505 --> 00:39:15,944
It lasted less than a year.

432
00:39:17,705 --> 00:39:19,065
He went abroad to study.

433
00:39:20,585 --> 00:39:23,305
I told him I was willing to wait,

434
00:39:23,384 --> 00:39:25,705
but he said I shouldn't waste my time.

435
00:39:27,025 --> 00:39:28,705
Also, he might meet someone better.

436
00:39:31,145 --> 00:39:32,864
When I saw him just now,

437
00:39:33,825 --> 00:39:35,545
he stood by what he said before

438
00:39:37,464 --> 00:39:40,345
and he's not sorry he said it.

439
00:39:45,145 --> 00:39:47,105
Maybe he was focusing on his future,

440
00:39:48,464 --> 00:39:50,785
but he obviously didn't love you enough.

441
00:39:50,864 --> 00:39:52,305
That's why he let you go.

442
00:39:53,345 --> 00:39:55,505
He and I are different people, you know?

443
00:39:55,585 --> 00:39:56,745
I know that.

444
00:39:56,825 --> 00:39:58,225
What are you afraid of then?

445
00:40:01,705 --> 00:40:03,545
What happened to you in the past

446
00:40:04,145 --> 00:40:05,705
made you lose faith in love,

447
00:40:08,384 --> 00:40:11,904
but I'm going to show you
how serious I am about you.

448
00:40:19,225 --> 00:40:20,705
People change.

449
00:40:21,505 --> 00:40:23,265
You're young. You have a lot to see.

450
00:40:25,545 --> 00:40:27,105
This is all I have to say.

451
00:40:29,185 --> 00:40:30,145
Hey.

452
00:40:30,225 --> 00:40:32,585
Hey, where are you going?

453
00:40:36,105 --> 00:40:37,065
Hey.

454
00:40:37,545 --> 00:40:38,745
So what if I'm young?

455
00:40:39,545 --> 00:40:41,145
I'll grow up one day.

456
00:40:44,665 --> 00:40:47,185
You're afraid I'll change,
but what about you?

457
00:40:47,864 --> 00:40:50,305
If you were to die tomorrow,
what would I do?

458
00:40:50,384 --> 00:40:51,424
Are you cursing me?

459
00:40:51,985 --> 00:40:53,185
I'm not cursing you.

460
00:40:53,785 --> 00:40:54,705
I'm serious.

461
00:40:56,585 --> 00:41:00,305
What are you afraid of? It just
complicates everything and wastes time.

462
00:41:00,384 --> 00:41:02,585
We don't know what will happen tomorrow.

463
00:41:03,145 --> 00:41:05,225
Why can't we just get together now?

464
00:41:18,944 --> 00:41:20,145
Where are you going?

465
00:41:20,225 --> 00:41:22,665
Can we talk this through?

466
00:41:23,705 --> 00:41:25,464
Wait.

467
00:41:25,545 --> 00:41:26,825
I'm going home.

468
00:41:32,464 --> 00:41:33,904
I need to water my plant,

469
00:41:33,985 --> 00:41:35,105
so it grows quickly,

470
00:41:35,185 --> 00:41:36,105
like someone I know.

471
00:41:45,424 --> 00:41:48,065
Are you agreeing to our relationship?

472
00:41:49,944 --> 00:41:50,785
Finally!

473
00:41:50,864 --> 00:41:52,785
I can't wait to eat some ivy gourd leaves.

474
00:41:52,864 --> 00:41:55,225
-Hooray.
-Let me down.

475
00:41:56,065 --> 00:41:59,345
We're in a park. Don't make so much noise.

476
00:41:59,424 --> 00:42:00,985
I'll refrain from making noise.

477
00:42:01,464 --> 00:42:03,265
-Let me kiss you instead.
-Don't.

478
00:42:03,345 --> 00:42:07,145
Stop it. Keep your hands to yourself.
Do you hear me?

479
00:42:07,225 --> 00:42:09,785
Look, there are people around.

480
00:42:11,505 --> 00:42:12,505
Okay?

481
00:42:13,105 --> 00:42:15,384
I love you. Let's go home, shall we?

482
00:42:15,464 --> 00:42:17,225
Come on.

483
00:42:17,305 --> 00:42:18,585
-Are you driving me?
-Yes.

484
00:42:18,665 --> 00:42:21,225
Get on my back.

485
00:42:21,745 --> 00:42:22,705
One, two, three.

486
00:42:23,545 --> 00:42:24,745
Let's go home.

487
00:42:37,225 --> 00:42:38,585
Let me help you.

488
00:42:44,065 --> 00:42:45,825
Are you thinking about last night?

489
00:42:47,785 --> 00:42:49,545
Why would I?

490
00:42:51,185 --> 00:42:54,424
You want to make things better, don't you?

491
00:42:56,065 --> 00:42:57,745
You get irritable with your mom,

492
00:42:58,625 --> 00:43:00,105
but you're not really angry.

493
00:43:00,985 --> 00:43:03,185
You just…

494
00:43:03,904 --> 00:43:05,145
hold a grudge.

495
00:43:06,944 --> 00:43:08,745
You've been holding onto it for so long

496
00:43:09,705 --> 00:43:11,625
and you can't seem to let it go, right?

497
00:43:13,265 --> 00:43:14,705
You're such a know-it-all.

498
00:43:15,665 --> 00:43:17,424
Someone once told me

499
00:43:18,384 --> 00:43:20,745
that families should try
to resolve their problems.

500
00:43:22,025 --> 00:43:23,825
If you love someone, you should say so.

501
00:43:24,384 --> 00:43:27,944
If you want to understand,
you should talk to each other.

502
00:43:28,745 --> 00:43:30,065
Mutual understanding

503
00:43:30,585 --> 00:43:32,464
requires an open mind.

504
00:43:33,345 --> 00:43:35,225
When did you get so smart?

505
00:43:36,625 --> 00:43:37,944
Do you like it?

506
00:43:39,025 --> 00:43:40,225
I like it.

507
00:43:40,705 --> 00:43:42,145
I like listening to your voice.

508
00:43:47,665 --> 00:43:48,705
Let me help.

509
00:44:10,705 --> 00:44:12,464
Don't do what you did yesterday.

510
00:44:14,545 --> 00:44:16,185
As long as Mom doesn't start it.

511
00:44:17,025 --> 00:44:18,424
Nut.

512
00:44:21,785 --> 00:44:23,825
All right. I won't.

513
00:44:24,785 --> 00:44:25,944
Are you satisfied now?

514
00:44:27,345 --> 00:44:28,505
I'm satisfied.

515
00:44:29,265 --> 00:44:31,065
You're very cute like this.

516
00:44:31,984 --> 00:44:33,585
If I'm cute, I want a reward.

517
00:44:50,424 --> 00:44:54,065
Let me think about what to give you.

518
00:44:59,944 --> 00:45:01,185
Kuenchai.

519
00:45:13,745 --> 00:45:14,944
Mrs. Na.

520
00:45:17,825 --> 00:45:18,745
Mom.

521
00:45:21,345 --> 00:45:22,464
I'll check upstairs.

522
00:45:25,705 --> 00:45:26,785
Mom.

523
00:45:33,345 --> 00:45:36,185
Sorry, the number you've dialed
cannot be reached--

524
00:45:36,265 --> 00:45:37,864
She's not upstairs.

525
00:45:39,585 --> 00:45:40,424
Sorry--

526
00:45:40,505 --> 00:45:42,944
Where did she go?
Why is her phone switched off?

527
00:45:45,625 --> 00:45:47,025
I forgot to tell you

528
00:45:47,585 --> 00:45:49,225
that her phone is broken.

529
00:45:52,984 --> 00:45:54,464
I'll go and ask the neighbors.

530
00:46:05,464 --> 00:46:08,345
Ms. Chair, do you know where Mrs. Na went?

531
00:46:11,625 --> 00:46:12,944
Ms. Chair.

532
00:46:17,384 --> 00:46:18,825
Ms. Chair.

533
00:46:19,585 --> 00:46:20,864
Ms. Chair.

534
00:46:29,745 --> 00:46:31,705
Chu and Nhong didn't see anything.

535
00:46:45,464 --> 00:46:46,585
Kuenchai.

536
00:46:56,384 --> 00:46:57,785
I have a doctor's appointment.

537
00:46:59,505 --> 00:47:00,904
I'm going to see the doctor.

538
00:47:02,464 --> 00:47:03,585
She is…

539
00:47:19,585 --> 00:47:22,025
I forgot your mom
had an appointment this month.

540
00:47:22,505 --> 00:47:25,185
I'm sorry for not taking good care of her.

541
00:47:25,665 --> 00:47:28,305
It's not your fault. It's my fault.

542
00:47:29,065 --> 00:47:31,265
You're worried about her too, aren't you?

543
00:47:32,065 --> 00:47:33,265
-Hi, there.
-Hello.

544
00:47:33,345 --> 00:47:34,904
Hi, Nut, Tofu.

545
00:47:34,984 --> 00:47:36,065
I came to pick Mom up.

546
00:47:36,665 --> 00:47:37,944
Really?

547
00:47:39,105 --> 00:47:41,785
I saw her going that way.

548
00:47:44,265 --> 00:47:46,265
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

549
00:47:56,145 --> 00:47:59,225
The psychiatrist sent me
the preliminary test results.

550
00:47:59,785 --> 00:48:01,105
You shouldn't worry.

551
00:48:01,625 --> 00:48:05,665
The symptoms you described
could have stemmed from several causes.

552
00:48:05,745 --> 00:48:09,065
It could be a side effect of the medicine.

553
00:48:09,145 --> 00:48:10,424
How about this?

554
