I wondered if he would be accepted,

820
01:10:28,624 --> 01:10:30,704
if anyone would love him.

821
01:10:33,784 --> 01:10:35,664
His dad couldn't accept it

822
01:10:36,744 --> 01:10:40,585
and blamed me
for not raising him properly.

823
01:10:41,985 --> 01:10:43,704
That's why I took his dad's side

824
01:10:44,825 --> 01:10:47,065
and forbade Nut from being himself.

825
01:10:48,704 --> 01:10:51,465
He's turning gay
because of your negligence.

826
01:10:51,545 --> 01:10:52,784
He's just a nice boy.

827
01:10:52,865 --> 01:10:54,465
Don't talk back to me.

828
01:10:54,545 --> 01:10:56,425
Boys have to be strong.

829
01:10:56,505 --> 01:10:59,065
What kind of mom are you?

830
01:10:59,145 --> 01:11:00,505
I'm not taking it.

831
01:11:01,664 --> 01:11:03,385
I don't want to be a soldier.

832
01:11:03,865 --> 01:11:06,305
If you won't be a soldier,
what do you want to be?

833
01:11:06,784 --> 01:11:07,985
Anything.

834
01:11:08,545 --> 01:11:10,425
I just don't want to be like Dad.

835
01:11:11,704 --> 01:11:13,265
Will you please

836
01:11:15,985 --> 01:11:17,345
listen to your dad?

837
01:11:17,425 --> 01:11:18,744
He wants the best for you.

838
01:11:19,985 --> 01:11:21,065
He wants the best?

839
01:11:22,664 --> 01:11:26,225
For me or himself?

840
01:11:27,465 --> 01:11:29,744
I was weak and selfish.

841
01:11:32,385 --> 01:11:33,905
As a mother,

842
01:11:33,985 --> 01:11:35,465
I should have sided with him

843
01:11:37,105 --> 01:11:39,025
and protected him.

844
01:11:40,465 --> 01:11:42,825
Instead, I trampled on his heart.

845
01:11:45,784 --> 01:11:48,105
I forced him to comply the way I did.

846
01:11:54,664 --> 01:11:56,704
I forbade him from being himself.

847
01:12:01,145 --> 01:12:03,704
I failed to support him.

848
01:12:19,825 --> 01:12:21,505
I know that you feel bad about it.

849
01:12:25,505 --> 01:12:27,744
But now that you've acknowledged
what happened,

850
01:12:29,744 --> 01:12:32,145
you feel better, don't you?

851
01:12:36,985 --> 01:12:39,025
If you want
to get anything off your chest,

852
01:12:40,345 --> 01:12:42,465
you can tell me.

853
01:12:43,784 --> 01:12:45,265
I'm willing to listen.

854
01:12:54,345 --> 01:12:55,865
After that day,

855
01:12:56,545 --> 01:12:58,505
Nut avoided me.

856
01:13:00,545 --> 01:13:03,105
He barely uttered a word to me.

857
01:13:05,585 --> 01:13:08,065
I never had a chance to apologize to him.

858
01:13:13,664 --> 01:13:16,345
After his dad passed away,
we became even more distant.

859
01:13:25,025 --> 01:13:25,945
Nut.

860
01:13:26,664 --> 01:13:28,545
Come for dinner. I'll warm it up.

861
01:13:29,545 --> 01:13:31,825
There's no need. I've eaten.

862
01:13:47,585 --> 01:13:48,664
Mom,

863
01:13:49,225 --> 01:13:50,784
I'm moving to a dorm next week.

864
01:14:57,225 --> 01:15:00,025
I knew that Nut moved here
because of my condition.

865
01:15:01,025 --> 01:15:03,945
He didn't want me to be reminded
of what had happened before.

866
01:15:08,704 --> 01:15:10,345
Despite our move,

867
01:15:11,385 --> 01:15:14,505
the distance between us didn't change.

868
01:15:25,945 --> 01:15:27,425
The longer it went on,

869
01:15:29,345 --> 01:15:32,824
the harder it became to heal the rift.

870
01:15:34,105 --> 01:15:35,905
Then I came to realize

871
01:15:38,105 --> 01:15:41,145
that Nut didn't need me anymore.

872
01:15:54,905 --> 01:15:57,145
I wronged him

873
01:16:00,784 --> 01:16:04,065
because I grew up in an unstable family.

874
01:16:05,784 --> 01:16:08,865
I wished for my own family to be perfect.

875
01:16:10,624 --> 01:16:13,585
But in this world, nothing is perfect.

876
01:16:14,545 --> 01:16:16,465
I used to fear

877
01:16:18,305 --> 01:16:21,465
that Nut was abnormal for being like this.

878
01:16:22,545 --> 01:16:25,225
In fact, being gay is normal.

879
01:16:29,305 --> 01:16:30,784
These days

880
01:16:33,225 --> 01:16:35,065
seeing him all grown up,

881
01:16:35,784 --> 01:16:38,105
capable of supporting himself…

882
01:16:39,065 --> 01:16:42,624
EXCLUSIVE INTERVIEW
WITH PEERANUT BURARAT

883
01:16:57,784 --> 01:16:59,065
…being accepted by others,

884
01:16:59,905 --> 01:17:02,265
with friends like everyone else…

885
01:17:02,345 --> 01:17:04,185
EXCLUSIVE INTERVIEW
WITH PEERANUT BURARAT

886
01:17:20,145 --> 01:17:22,425
I've realized that kids
should be themselves.

887
01:17:24,225 --> 01:17:26,744
They should be allowed
to choose their own paths

888
01:17:28,185 --> 01:17:31,945
with the support of their parents,

889
01:17:32,985 --> 01:17:34,664
without being under control.

890
01:17:35,824 --> 01:17:38,025
A child's life is their own,

891
01:17:38,585 --> 01:17:40,305
not their parents'.

892
01:17:44,065 --> 01:17:46,784
You accepted who he was long ago, right?

893
01:17:49,025 --> 01:17:51,225
That's why you could accept me.

894
01:17:51,905 --> 01:17:55,225
I never wanted to kick you out
like Nut always feared.

895
01:17:56,465 --> 01:18:00,465
I'm actually thankful
for your presence in our life.

896
01:18:02,425 --> 01:18:04,824
I no longer care about
what others might say.

897
01:18:06,225 --> 01:18:07,744
The smile on his face

898
01:18:08,305 --> 01:18:11,025
makes me realize what makes him happy

899
01:18:11,664 --> 01:18:13,945
and what makes me happy.

900
01:18:17,185 --> 01:18:21,065
Thank you
for throwing me a birthday party.

901
01:18:22,945 --> 01:18:24,065
Do you like it?

902
01:18:25,744 --> 01:18:26,585
Yes.

903
01:18:27,744 --> 01:18:29,185
Do you like the party

904
01:18:29,664 --> 01:18:31,225
or me?

905
01:18:33,824 --> 01:18:35,025
What a cheap shot.

906
01:18:37,824 --> 01:18:39,585
When you asked me what I wanted

907
01:18:39,664 --> 01:18:41,664
for my birthday

908
01:18:42,465 --> 01:18:44,065
and I said nothing,

909
01:18:48,465 --> 01:18:50,145
that's because

910
01:18:52,225 --> 01:18:53,744
I already have you.

911
01:18:59,624 --> 01:19:01,585
Stay by my side…

912
01:19:04,345 --> 01:19:05,865
and don't go anywhere.

913
01:19:15,105 --> 01:19:16,945
Thank you so much

914
01:19:18,225 --> 01:19:20,145
for making him happy.

915
01:19:22,465 --> 01:19:26,784
You make him laugh and smile
like I haven't seen him do for so long.

916
01:19:30,225 --> 01:19:31,585
Also,

917
01:19:33,824 --> 01:19:35,624
thank you…

918
01:19:38,465 --> 01:19:40,105
for being there for me

919
01:19:40,905 --> 01:19:43,465
and supporting me through all this.

920
01:19:48,704 --> 01:19:52,065
If I hadn't been sick, I would have
been able to talk to him more.

921
01:19:53,065 --> 01:19:56,265
Now that I feel better
and I'm thinking straight,

922
01:19:57,305 --> 01:19:58,985
it seems like it's too late.

923
01:20:00,945 --> 01:20:02,744
It's never too late.

924
01:20:05,145 --> 01:20:07,305
You can always start over.

925
01:20:08,385 --> 01:20:10,225
You can do that right this minute.

926
01:20:34,784 --> 01:20:35,945
Shall we go home?

927
01:20:38,105 --> 01:20:39,025
Let's go.

928
01:21:22,305 --> 01:21:24,105
How about this?

929
01:21:24,585 --> 01:21:26,225
Think about it.

930
01:21:26,704 --> 01:21:28,305
From what you've written,

931
01:21:28,385 --> 01:21:30,065
the mother and her son

932
01:21:30,145 --> 01:21:32,105
don't really show it,

933
01:21:33,425 --> 01:21:34,865
but I can tell for sure

934
01:21:35,905 --> 01:21:37,425
that they still love each other.

935
01:21:41,025 --> 01:21:42,704
Do you think I should revise it?

936
01:21:43,265 --> 01:21:45,185
You should ask yourself that.

937
01:21:46,145 --> 01:21:48,664
You're the one writing it.

938
01:21:49,585 --> 01:21:52,985
How the relationship
between the mom and her son will turn out

939
01:21:53,664 --> 01:21:55,305
is not up to me.

940
01:21:56,185 --> 01:21:57,744
It's up to you.

941
01:22:55,025 --> 01:22:57,025
You came home late today, Nut.

942
01:22:59,824 --> 01:23:02,185
I thought we might go out for a walk.

943
01:23:02,865 --> 01:23:04,744
I took a walk with your mom.

944
01:23:04,824 --> 01:23:06,545
We talked about many things.

945
01:23:14,105 --> 01:23:16,225
She knows about us.

946
01:23:18,905 --> 01:23:20,784
She's not opposed to it.

947
01:23:23,905 --> 01:23:26,664
Perhaps she doesn't say anything,

948
01:23:27,704 --> 01:23:29,585
not because she doesn't care,

949
01:23:31,265 --> 01:23:34,025
but because she accepts who you are.

950
01:23:41,664 --> 01:23:42,985
I know

951
01:23:43,465 --> 01:23:45,065
that you're staying silent

952
01:23:45,545 --> 01:23:47,385
because you're thinking.

953
01:23:51,025 --> 01:23:52,945
Your mom is like this too.

954
01:23:54,385 --> 01:23:56,465
If you listen carefully,

955
01:23:57,265 --> 01:23:58,905
the silence

956
01:23:59,585 --> 01:24:02,585
may hide deep love and concern.

957
01:24:06,145 --> 01:24:09,664
Don't you think you should give yourself

958
01:24:10,624 --> 01:24:12,905
and give your mom a chance?

959
01:24:18,744 --> 01:24:20,185
You're quite the philosopher.

960
01:24:22,305 --> 01:24:23,505
Are you talking now?

961
01:24:28,824 --> 01:24:30,985
Today, your mom had sore feet.

962
01:24:32,385 --> 01:24:34,505
Shall we buy her new shoes tomorrow?

963
01:25:03,905 --> 01:25:05,065
Mrs. Na?

964
01:25:09,985 --> 01:25:13,265
I came to tell you to dress up tomorrow.

965
01:25:13,345 --> 01:25:14,225
Yes?

966
01:25:16,105 --> 01:25:16,985
Why?

967
01:25:17,065 --> 01:25:20,225
Well, we are going shopping tomorrow.

968
01:25:20,305 --> 01:25:21,505
Nut is taking us.

969
01:25:22,065 --> 01:25:22,985
Really?

970
01:26:13,145 --> 01:26:15,145
Is this outfit okay, Tofu?

971
01:26:16,985 --> 01:26:19,704
I don't go out much.
I only have old clothes.

972
01:26:20,865 --> 01:26:21,945
You look great.

973
01:26:24,345 --> 01:26:25,225
Where's Nut?

974
01:26:30,145 --> 01:26:31,065
He…

975
01:26:43,545 --> 01:26:46,345
Are they both your sons?
They're so handsome.

976
01:26:46,824 --> 01:26:47,824
Yes.

977
01:26:48,505 --> 01:26:49,824
He is my son.

978
01:26:51,185 --> 01:26:52,704
He is also my son.

979
01:26:55,065 --> 01:26:58,545
Tarn told me
that he wanted Nut to be happy,

980
01:26:59,505 --> 01:27:01,185
and what happened between them

981
01:27:01,865 --> 01:27:05,744
should just be left as a happy memory.

982
01:27:06,704 --> 01:27:09,185
He was the one who made me understand

983
01:27:09,265 --> 01:27:10,905
that being gay isn't a disease.

984
01:27:11,545 --> 01:27:12,864
It's not down to bad karma,

985
01:27:14,265 --> 01:27:15,744
or an emotional disorder.

986
01:27:16,465 --> 01:27:18,585
And it's not a joke.

987
